news.headline: Active Vs. Passive In The Era Of AI Valuations
news.summary: Passive investors have become momentum traders, cheering on the same few winners. If these companies stumble or the AI narrative fades, passive investors could face meaningful drawdowns.

news.headline: Small Businesses Concerned Over Quality
news.summary: The NFIB's Small Business Optimism Index reading came in weaker than expected, at 98.2 versus forecasts of 98.3. Of the inputs, the most concerning decline was in actual earnings changes.

news.summary: Read why the current bull market may yet last years, with low recession risk and tech-driven growth.

news.headline: NFIB Small Business Survey: Optimism Declines As Uncertainty Eases
news.summary: The NFIB Small Business Optimism Index fell for a second straight month in October, dropping 0.6 points to 98.2. This was below the forecast of 98.5 and marks the lowest level in six months.
